cs.AI, cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.DS, cs.CG

Reasoning: 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is the most likely category as the paper discusses the application of logic and Boolean-derived methods in producing a logical programming of arbitrary range, precision, and dimensionality, which is relevant to AI.
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is also a likely category as the paper explores the Disjunctive Normal Form representation of logic table expansions and extends it to a real-valued logic model.
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is relevant as the paper discusses logical programming and the production of a game character's logic in mathematical form.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is relevant as the paper discusses the utilization of quantities on the range [0,1], [-1,1], [a,b], (x,y), (x,y,z), and etc. which can be seen as data structures.
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is relevant as the paper discusses the production of a game character's logic in mathematical form, which may involve spatial constructs.
